<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=5853&amp;p=54167#p54167"><![CDATA[
A new version of XPMCK (an MML compiler kit) is available, with some Gameboy related items in the changelog..<br /><br />    * Added a more convenient syntax for writing volume macros.<br />    * Added an alternative volume control mode for the Gameboy target.<br />    * Added the ability to set the number of sweep steps for @te on the Gameboy.<br />    * Added a way of quickly offsetting or scaling macro values.<br />    * Fixed a bug in the handling of @ve which would cause compilation to fail if a positive direction was set. <br /><br />The "alternative volume control" mentioned above is the so-called "zombie mode".<br /><br />Link: <a href="http://jiggawatt.org/muzak/xpmck/" class="postlink">http://jiggawatt.org/muzak/xpmck/</a><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1181">mic_</a> â€” Fri Dec 18, 2009 2:36 pm</p><hr />
